// Man page for htop
manHtop="HTOP(1)                          X Shell Manual                          HTOP(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    htop - Interactive process viewer
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>htop</b> [deploy]
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Display active processes of the operating system in real-time.
    The deploy subcommand launches htop as a background process, allowing
    continued shell use. Without deploy, use CTRLC to exit.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>deploy</b> - Background Mode
      Launch htop as a background process.
      Allows continued shell interaction while monitoring processes.
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <b>htop</b>
    Run process viewer (CTRLC to exit)

    <b>htop deploy</b>
    Launch as background process
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>spawn</b>, <b>gmon</b>"